description: From French chebec, from Spanish xabeque or Catalan xabec or Italian sciabecco, from Arabic شُبَّاك‎ (šubbāk, “fishing-net”). Not to confuse with the sambuq, an Indian-Sea vessel.

entries.meaning: A small two-masted, and later three-masted, Mediterranean transport ship with an overhanging bow and stern. [from mid 18th c.]
